sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: AND gate structure for regulation of E.coli in CF mucus
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device will have the cells live in the presence of LasL and Sialic acid
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This design will produce one of two necessary transcription factors for the HrpL AND gate. This will produce it in the presence of Sialic Acid
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: we wanted a Negative Feed Back loop
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device will detect the presence of LasL which is a signaling molecule used by P. aeruginosa. This is tied to make HrpR which is needed in the HrpL AND gate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39019
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device, in the presence of HrpS and HrpR, will produce the regulator TetR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In the absence of tetR, this device will make granulysin and DNase1 which will kill the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: we needed to have a way to make sure both the membrane and genome of the cell was destroyed. These enzymes seemed like the best idea.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter sequence for the NanR transcription factor in the Nan Operon. This Operon is for Sialic Acid Degradation. Promoter is for E.Coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This codes for the NanR Regulator. This is the the repressor for the Nan Operon and is turned off by the presence of sialic acid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This allows the transport of Sialic Acid into the cell
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: These are the enzymes needed for Sialic Acid breakdown in E.Coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Since these are all on an operon, we made sure there was sufficient space and an RBS in-between each coding region
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This codes for one of the two necessary genes (HrpS and HrpR) that will be needed to activate the HrpL AND gate
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the LasL protein which is used in P. aeruginosa quorum sensing
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: the promoter region for LasL regulator protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codes for HrpR. This is one of two proteins (HrpS and HrpR) needed for the HrpL AND gate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding region for the TetR repressor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This promoter sequence requires both HrpR and HrpS to be expressed for itself to be active. This functions as a digital AND gate
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39020
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for enzyme that degrades membrane
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M39021
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for DNase1, enzyme with unspecific degradation of ds DNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Edgar Aranda-Michel
